    <h1>
      Getting started
    </h1>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
      Minimum hardware requirements:<br>
      <ul>
       <li>500 MHz ix86 Prozessor *</li>
       <li>256 MB RAM</li>
       <li>3D accelerator card (a driver from the vendor is recommended because they are those which give the best
performance)
       <li>Optional: Sound card</li>
     </ul>
     Minimum software requirements:
     <ul>
        <li><a href="http://www.xfree86.org" target="_blank">XFree 4.x server</a> (with OpenGL support, 4.3 and Xrandr for resolution changing)</li>
        <li><a href="http://www.xfree86.org" target="_blank">OpenGL <a> the OpenGL library (should be included in your XFree Server or graphics card driver)</li>
        <li><a href="http://www.trolltech.com" target="_blank">QT 3.1</a> or better</li>
        <li><a href="http://www.kde.org" target="_blank">kdelibs 3.1</a> or better (3.0 is untested)</li>
        <li><a href="http://lib3ds.sourceforge.net" target="_blank">lib3ds</a> (Units and building rendering)</li>
        <li><a href="http://www.python.org" target="_blank">Python 2.0</a> or better (2.3 is recommended) </li>
        <li><a href="http://www.openal.org" target="_blank"> OpenAL (audio library)</li>
        <li><a href="http://www.thewml.org" target="_blank">WML</a> - For the handbook, if you don't use a binary package</li>
        <li>Image::Magick - For the handbook technologie dependency tree image, if you don't use a binary package and want this image.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
    * We've never tested Boson on other platforms but it should work.<br>
    &nbsp; Please send bug/sucesses reports to our <a href="mailto:boson-devel@lists.sourceforge.net">mailing list</a>.
    <p>
      Please note that since we do not yet provide precompiled binaries you will
      need to install the development packages of these libraries as well (the
      development packages usually have a -devel or -dev in their name).<br>
    </p>
    <p>
      Now you can download boson - for instructions see <a href="http://boson.eu.org/download.php">http://boson.eu.org/download.php</a>.<br>
      You need at least the packages &quot;code&quot; and &quot;data&quot;,
      &quot;music&quot; is optional.
    </p>

